r an untracked file should be deleted is duplicated between `Rewind()` (lines 338-358 of `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go`) and `PreviewRewind()` (lines 534-545 of the same file). Both methods iterate `untrackedNow` and apply the same three-check filter:\\n\\n```go\\n// In Rewind(), lines 338-353:\\nfor _, relPath := range untrackedNow {\\n    if checkpointFiles[relPath] { continue }\\n    if trackedFiles[relPath]    { continue }\\n    if preservedUntrackedFiles[relPath] { continue }\\n    // ... delete the file\\n}\\n\\n// In PreviewRewind(), lines 534-545:\\nfor _, relPath := range untrackedNow {\\n    if checkpointFiles[relPath] { continue }\\n    if trackedFiles[relPath]    { continue }\\n    if preservedUntrackedFiles[relPath] { continue }\\n    filesToDelete = append(filesToDelete, relPath)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdditionally, both methods share nearly identical preamble code: opening the repository, getting the checkpoint commit/tree, loading preserved untracked files from session state, building `checkpointFiles` and `trackedFiles` maps from the tree and HEAD. This is roughly 50 lines of duplicated setup.\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Extract a helper function that returns the list of files that would be deleted on rewind. Something like:\\n\\n```go\\n// filesToDeleteOnRewind returns untracked files that are not in the checkpoint,\\n// not tracked by HEAD, and not preserved from session start.\\nfunc filesToDeleteOnRewind(\\n    checkpointFiles, trackedFiles, preservedUntrackedFiles map[string]bool,\\n) ([]string, error) {\\n    untrackedNow, err := gitUntrackedFiles()\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil, err\\n    }\\n    var result []string\\n    for _, relPath := range untrackedNow {\\n        if checkpointFiles[relPath] || trackedFiles[relPath] || preservedUntrackedFiles[relPath] {\\n            continue\\n        }\\n        result = append(result, relPath)\\n    }\\n    return result, nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`Rew