ent since the integration tests cover the critical paths.\\n\\n**No action needed:**\\n\\n- The behavioral change (excluding gitignored files) is architecturally sound and properly tested.\\n- The placement in `common.go` is correct.\\n- The git CLI usage is consistent with established patterns.\\n- The error handling in `Rewind()` is appropriate.\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"d13943d3-e9d8-4ea0-89a6-e6ccc052a928\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"217e8e42-7730-423f-8dae-1db1f82396ac\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"be7201dc-0742-46dc-83f7-b77432d86dbe\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"transient-mapping-sparrow\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_018wsB3H65kHJgumZGPjFzSU\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"All 5 agents are done. Here's the synthesized review:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Review Synthesis\\n\\n### P1 -- Should Fix Before Merge\\n\\n**1. Use `-z` flag for NUL-separated output** (Security)\\n`git ls-files` output is split on `\\\\n`, but filenames can legally contain newlines. The codebase already handles this correctly in `checkpoint/temporary.go` using `-z`. Use `git ls-files --others --exclude-standard -z` and split on `\\\\x00` instead.\\n\\n### P2 -- Should Fix\\n\\n**2. Remove the `collectUntrackedFiles` wrapper** (Simplicity + Architecture)\\nAll 5 agents flagged this. It's a one-line passthrough that creates two names for the same operation. Either:\\n- (a) Rename `gitUntrackedFiles` to `collectUntrackedFiles` and have all 3 call sites use it, or\\n- (b) Remove the wrapper and update the one caller in `manual_commit_session.go`\\n\\n**3. Capture stderr on git failure** (Pattern Recognition)\\n`cmd.Output()` discards stderr. Other git CLI wrappers in the codebase (e.g., `HardResetWithProtection`) include stderr in error messages. Include `exitErr.Stderr` in the error for debuggability.\\n\